-- в”Ђв”Ђ Planka в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Planka is a self-hosted, real-time Kanban board built as an open, fair-code alternative to Trello, developed by PLANKA Software GmbH in Germany.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (self-hosted Community Edition); Pro plans priced separately$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2019, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Small team (PLANKA Software GmbH; exact team size not publicly disclosed)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Kempten, Germany$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$German$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Planka Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Planka self-hosted Kanban board: real-time boards, Docker deployment, Community vs Pro pricing, features and alternatives like Trello and Wekan compared.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Planka is a self-hosted, real-time Kanban board application positioned as an open alternative to Trello, developed by PLANKA Software GmbH, a company headquartered in Kempten, Germany. The open-source Community Edition, hosted on GitHub since 2019 and accumulating more than 11,000 stars, is free to self-host via Docker or other deployment methods and gives teams full control over their data and infrastructure. Planka's code is source-available under a 'Fair Use License' (a fair-code license rather than a traditional OSI-approved open-source license), which permits free use for personal, internal-organizational, non-profit and educational purposes but restricts operating Planka as a hosted service for third parties or sharing a single license across unrelated companies without a commercial Pro license. In 2025 the company introduced a Pro Edition aimed at teams that need higher scalability, advanced professional features and premium support, available either self-hosted or as a fully managed cloud offering, alongside a paid installation service (starting around EUR 469 plus VAT) for teams that want PLANKA configured on their own server or cloud environment. Core functionality includes unlimited boards and cards, real-time synchronization across users, background and card customization, and an interface that has been translated into 35-plus languages by its community. Planka targets small to mid-sized teams, privacy-conscious organizations, and self-hosting enthusiasts who want Trello-style Kanban boards without sending data to a third-party SaaS vendor, as well as agencies and companies that prefer to run project-management tools inside their own infrastructure for compliance or cost reasons. Its closest competitors in the self-hosted Kanban space include Wekan (a fully open-source, MIT-licensed alternative) and Focalboard, and, in the broader hosted Kanban category, Trello itself along with Jira and Asana's board views. Planka differentiates itself with a clean, modern interface closely modeled on Trello's UX, straightforward Docker-based deployment, and a licensing model that keeps the core product free for internal use while monetizing hosting, scale and support through its newer Pro tier rather than gating basic Kanban functionality behind a paywall.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'bfc32b77-2902-4a87-8ab8-27743eb3989b';

